  "enhanced_information": "In the case of a 9-year-old boy with uncomplicated pulmonary tuberculosis on isoniazid, rifampin, and ethambutol, the following points are relevant: 1) His 3-year-old sibling should receive INH prophylaxis as they are at risk of tuberculosis transmission from the boy. 2) A baseline auditory function test is not essential before initiating treatment, as ethambutol primarily poses a risk for optic neuritis rather than auditory issues. 3) Polyarthralgia is not a commonly recognized adverse effect of isoniazid or rifampin; it is more associated with other medications or conditions. 4) If the mother is not infected with tuberculosis, she does not require INH prophylaxis. Therefore, the most accurate statement is that the sibling should receive INH prophylaxis."
